<TheLesson
	title='Overview of Financial Planning'
	scene='planning-a-budget'
	gradientColor='var(--green-3)'>
	<InteractiveActivity
		client:load
		title='What Is Financial Planning To You?'
		setActivityType={'reflection'}
		prompts={[
			'Before we start, What does that term, financial planning, mean to you? How would you define it? Why?',
		]}
	/>
	<StaticContent title='What Is Financial Planning?'>
		<p>
			Do you want to buy a new iPhone, a new car, or your own house? Do you want
			to begin reducing your debt instead of increasing it? Do you want to keep
			growing your wealth? If you answered yes to even one of these questions,
			financial planning could be the answer! Whatever your goals, life is
			complicated and risky, and having a well-developed financial plan
			increases the odds of achieving your goals.
		</p>
		<SubSection title='Financial Planning Defined'>
			<p>
				The idea of financial planning is really no different from the idea of
				planning most anything. It is an ongoing process that looks at your
				current financial situation and creates strategies to reach your
				financial goals.
			</p>
			<p>
				Financial planning often delves into multiple areas of finance,
				including investing, taxes, savings, retirement, real estate, insurance,
				and more. A financial plan has to be re-evaluated, adjusted, and
				re-adjusted. The earlier you start, the better off you will be!
			</p>
		</SubSection>
	</StaticContent>
	<StaticContent title='Factors Affecting Financial Planning'>
		<p>
			There are many factors that can affect financial planning. These factors
			can range from what can be considered small (micro factors) to relatively
			large (macro factors).
		</p>
		<SideBySideText>
			<SubSection
				title='Micro Factors'
				optionalClass='littleCircle'
				slot='a'>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<p>Family Structure</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>Health</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>Age/Life Stage</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>Career Choice (covered in Module 2)</p>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</SubSection>
			<SubSection
				title='Macro Factors'
				optionalClass='bigCircle'
				slot='b'>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<p>Business Cycles</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>Labor Market</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>Currency Value</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>Other economic performance indicators</p>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</SubSection>
		</SideBySideText>
		<SubSection title='How You Benefit From Financial Planning '>
			<p>Financial planning can:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<p>
						Prevent devastating mistakes (e.g., poor credit, bankruptcy, housing
						foreclosure)
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>Prepare you for emergencies</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>Help you to be financially secure later in life</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</SubSection>
	</StaticContent>
	<StaticContent title='Six Steps To the Financial Planning Process'>
		<p>There are six essential steps to the financial planning process:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>
				<p>Define goals</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Assess your current situation</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Identify and evaluate plans that could achieve your goals</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Select and implement the best plan</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Evaluate your financial plan</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Revise your financial plan (annually)</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
	</StaticContent>
	<StaticContent title='Step 1: Define Goals'>
		<p>Define by timing of goals:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>
				<p>Short-term (1–2 years)</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Intermediate (2–10 years)</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Long-term (beyond 10 years)</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
		<p>
			Create a S.M.A.R.T Goal: A truly useful goal must be Specific, Measurable,
			Attainable, Relevant, and Time-bound
		</p>
		<SubSection title='S.M.A.R.T Goal Example'>
			<dl>
				<dt>Goal:</dt>
				<dd>To Wake up earlier</dd>
				<dt>Specific:</dt>
				<dd>
					I want to wake up earlier each morning to have more time for my
					morning routine.
				</dd>
				<dt>Measurable:</dt>
				<dd>
					I will start setting my alarm clock for 7:30 AM this week, and each
					week set it earlier by 15 minutes. Plus, I will write the time when I
					actually woke up on my calendar to measure progress.
				</dd>
				<dt>Attainable:</dt>
				<dd>
					My schedule allows me to go to bed at a decent time each night, so
					waking up earlier will not take away many hours of rest.
				</dd>
				<dt>Relevant:</dt>
				<dd>
					My morning routine is filled with social media, and I feel rushed
					trying to get to work each day, so waking up early would help me feel
					calmer.
				</dd>
				<dt>Time-bound:</dt>
				<dd>
					In four weeks, I want to wake up one hour earlier than when I usually
					wake up now.
				</dd>
			</dl>
		</SubSection>
	</StaticContent>
	<StaticContent title='Step 2: Assess Your Current Situation'>
		<p>Questions for you to consider:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>
				<p>Are you a big spender or a big saver?</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					Your saving accounts for what <TextStyle setType={'strong emphasis'}>
						percentage
					</TextStyle> of your after-tax income?
				</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
		<CallOut
			setColor={'green'}
			isCentered>
			<p>This formula helps you determine your after-income savings:</p>
			<MathEq
				isDisplayMode
